<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3375758>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Sclerothyone reichi sp. nov., holotype (MZUSP 1644). (A) lateral view of the body (mouth in red arrow and anus white arrow); (B) anal papillae (black arrow) and (C) calcareous ring; (D) body wall table in upper view (E) and lower view (F); introvert wall table in upper view; (G) rosette from introvert; (H) rod from tentacle and (I) end plate from tube feet. R, radial plate; IR, interradial plate; labels on calcareous ring follow Ludwig’s (1889–1892) scheme. Scale bars: A, 10mm; B–C, 1mm; D–E 50 μm; F–G, 30 μm; H, 50 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3375758/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

